The script below takes in an image (mosaic.tif) and produces a histogram and csv containing all the angles. The angles are corrected to correspond to those by RFT.
clear;  
I = imread('mosaic.tif');  
complement = imcomplement(I);  
BW = imbinarize(complement);  
out = bwskel(BW);  
mn=bwmorph(out,'branchpoints');

branches = out & ~mn;  
imshow(branches);  
sts = regionprops( branches, "Orientation", "Area");  
figure;  
angles = [];  
for i = 1:length(sts)  
    if sts(i).Orientation < 0  
        angles = [angles repmat(sts(i).Orientation+180, 1, sts(i).Area)];  
